* {{cite book|last1=Berrigan|first1=Daniel|author-mask=1|title=America Is Hard to Find|date=1972|publisher=Doubleday|location=Garden City, N.Y.|isbn=978-0-385-00327-8|edition=1st|OCLC=427586}}
* {{cite book|last1=Berrigan|first1=Daniel|author-mask=with|last2=Berrigan|first2=Philip (Foreword)|title=Prison Poems|date=1973|publisher=Unicorn Press|location=Greensboro, N.C.|isbn=978-0-87775-049-9|edition=2nd|OCLC=726986}}
* {{cite book|last1=Berrigan|first1=Daniel|author-mask=with|last2=Lockwood|first2=Lee|title=Daniel Berrigan: Absurd Convictions, Modest Hopes; Conversations after prison with Lee Lockwood|date=1973|publisher=Vintage Books|location=New York|isbn=978-0-394-71912-2|edition=1st|OCLC=851142578}}
* {{cite book|last1=Berrigan|first1=Daniel|author-mask=with|last2=Nhất Hạnh|first2=Thich|title=The Raft Is Not the Shore: Conversations Toward a Buddhist-Christian Awareness|date=1975|publisher=Beacon Press|location=Boston|isbn=978-1-57075-344-2|edition=New York: Orbis Books, 2001|OCLC=923481583}} 
