This is a list of the British [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal Party]], [[SDP–Liberal Alliance]], and [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] general election manifestos since the [[United Kingdom general election, 1900|1900 general election]].
From 1900 to 1918, the Liberal general election manifesto was usually published as a form of a short personal address by the [[Leader of the Liberal Party (UK)|leader of the Party]]. From 1922 the party usually published a more formal document.
From the 1900 election to the [[United Kingdom general election, 1979|1979 election]] the party went to the polls as the Liberal Party. In 1983 and 1987, the party went to the polls under the banner of the "Alliance", as a result of the pact between the Liberals and the [[Social Democratic Party (UK)|Social Democratic Party]], which formed in 1981. Since 1992 it has polled as the Liberal Democrats, due to the merger of the Liberals and the SDP in 1988.
From 2010 to 2015, the Liberal Democrats, having signed [[Conservative–Liberal Democrat coalition agreement|an agreement]] with the Conservatives, served as junior partner in the first [[coalition government]] since the Second World War.
{{Legend|#99FF99|Liberals win a [[Majority government|majority]].}} {{Legend|#FFB|Liberals win the most seats without an absolute majority.}}
