'''NUCMC''' is the abbreviation for the '''National Union Catalog of Manuscript Collections'''. It is a national-level program based at the [[Library of Congress]] that seeks to promote free access to the documentary heritage of the [[United States]]. It does this by providing [[cataloging]] for [[archives]] and historical societies around the country that do not have access to national online databases.<ref name="loc">{{cite web|url=https://www.loc.gov/coll/nucmc/eligible.html|publisher=loc.gov|title=How to Participate: National Union Catalog of Manuscript Collections - Library of Congress|accessdate=2017-02-06}}</ref> The program started in 1959 and published bound volumes of cataloging records until 1993. As of 1986, the cataloging records were input into [[Research Libraries Group|RLIN]], the Research Libraries Information Network, an international online database. As of September 2007, all cataloging records in RLIN have been migrated into the [[OCLC]] database ([[WorldCat]]), since RLIN was merged into OCLC. All cataloging since that time has been input into OCLC. It is not related to the [[National Union Catalog|NUC]] Pre-1956 volumes.<ref name="loc2">{{cite web|url=https://www.loc.gov/coll/nucmc/newfaqs.html#14|publisher=loc.gov|title=Frequently Asked Questions: National Union Catalog of Manuscript Collections (NUCMC), Library of Congress|accessdate=2017-02-06}}</ref>
==References== {{reflist}}
