'''Photothermal time''' ('''PTT''') is a product between [[growing degree-day]]s (GDD) and [[day length]] (hours) for each day. PTT = GDD × DL<ref>.{{Cite journal|last=Ravi Kumar|first=S.|last2=Hammer|first2=Graeme L.|last3=Broad|first3=Ian|last4=Harland|first4=Peter|last5=McLean|first5=Greg|date=2009-03|title=Modelling environmental effects on phenology and canopy development of diverse sorghum genotypes|url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0378429008002347|journal=Field Crops Research|volume=111|issue=1-2|pages=157–165|doi=10.1016/j.fcr.2008.11.010|issn=0378-4290}}</ref> It can be used to quantify [[environment (biophysical)|environment]],<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Li|first=Xin|last2=Guo|first2=Tingting|last3=Mu|first3=Qi|last4=Li|first4=Xianran|last5=Yu|first5=Jianming|date=2018-06-07|title=Genomic and environmental determinants and their interplay underlying phenotypic plasticity|url=http://www.pnas.org/content/early/2018/06/06/1718326115|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|language=en|pages=201718326|doi=10.1073/pnas.1718326115|issn=0027-8424|pmid=29891664}}</ref> as well as the timing of developmental stages of [[plant]]s.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Wilczek|first=Amity M.|last2=Roe|first2=Judith L.|last3=Knapp|first3=Mary C.|last4=Cooper|first4=Martha D.|last5=Lopez-Gallego|first5=Cristina|last6=Martin|first6=Laura J.|last7=Muir|first7=Christopher D.|last8=Sim|first8=Sheina|last9=Walker|first9=Alexis|date=2009-02-13|title=Effects of Genetic Perturbation on Seasonal Life History Plasticity|url=http://science.sciencemag.org/content/323/5916/930|journal=Science|language=en|volume=323|issue=5916|pages=930–934|doi=10.1126/science.1165826|issn=0036-8075|pmid=19150810}}</ref>

